7045	[Un-augmented {\v C}ech cochain complex on \(X\)]
7046	  \label{def:cech_complex_on_X}
7047	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.cechComplexOnX}
7048	  \uses{def:cech_nerve, def:relative_cech_complex_of_nerve}
7049	  \textit{Project-local.}
7050	  Given an open cover \(\mathcal{U}\) of \(X\) and a sheaf of \(\mathcal{O}_X\)-modules \(\mathcal{F}\),
7051	  the \emph{un-augmented {\v C}ech cochain complex}
7052	  \[
7053	    \mathcal{C}^0 \to \mathcal{C}^1 \to \mathcal{C}^2 \to \cdots
7054	  \]
7055	  on \(X\) is the alternating-coface-map cochain complex of the cosimplicial \(\mathcal{O}_X\)-module
7056	  obtained by forgetting the augmentation of the {\v C}ech nerve of Definition~\ref{def:cech_nerve}
7057	  (its \(\mathrm{Augmented.drop}\)). Its degree-\(p\) term is \(\mathcal{C}^p =
7058	  \prod_{(i_0, \ldots, i_p)} (j_{i_0 \ldots i_p})_*\bigl(\mathcal{F}|_{U_{i_0 \ldots i_p}}\bigr)\),
7059	  exactly as in the relative {\v C}ech complex of
7060	  Definition~\ref{def:relative_cech_complex_of_nerve} specialised to \(f = \mathrm{id}_X\).
7061	\end{definition}
