7066	[Augmentation point isomorphism]
7067	  \label{def:cech_nerve_point_iso}
7068	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.cechNervePointIso}
7069	  \uses{def:cech_nerve}
7070	  \textit{Project-local.}
7071	  The augmentation point of the {\v C}ech nerve of Definition~\ref{def:cech_nerve} is the value of the
7072	  nerve at the initial augmentation object, namely \((\mathrm{id}_X)_* (\mathrm{id}_X)^* \mathcal{F}\).
7073	  The \emph{augmentation point isomorphism} is the canonical isomorphism
7074	  \[
7075	    (\mathrm{CechNerve}\ \mathcal{U}\ \mathcal{F}).\mathrm{left} \;\cong\; \mathcal{F}
7076	  \]
7077	  obtained by composing the pullback unitor \((\mathrm{id}_X)^* \mathcal{F} \cong \mathcal{F}\) with the
7078	  pushforward unitor \((\mathrm{id}_X)_* \mathcal{G} \cong \mathcal{G}\) of the push--pull adjunction.
7079	\end{definition}
