7084	[{\v C}ech augmentation map]
7085	  \label{def:cech_augmentation}
7086	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.cechAugmentation}
7087	  \uses{def:cech_nerve_point_iso, def:cech_complex_on_X}
7088	  \textit{Project-local.}
7089	  The \emph{{\v C}ech augmentation} is the morphism \(\varepsilon : \mathcal{F} \to \mathcal{C}^0\) of
7090	  sheaves of \(\mathcal{O}_X\)-modules obtained by composing the inverse of the augmentation point
7091	  isomorphism of Definition~\ref{def:cech_nerve_point_iso} with the degree-\(0\) component of the
7092	  nerve's augmentation natural transformation (which lands in the degree-\(0\) term \(\mathcal{C}^0\) of
7093	  the complex of Definition~\ref{def:cech_complex_on_X}).
